title: Tamkin Khalilzade
text:
Tamkin Khalilzade (; born on 6 August 1993) is an <a href="Azerbaijan">Azerbaijan</a>i professional <a href="association%20football">football</a> <a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29">defender</a> who plays for <a href="Zira%20FK">Zira</a> and the <a href="Azerbaijan%20national%20football%20team">Azerbaijan national football team</a>.
Club career.
Khalilzade was born in <a href="Baku">Baku</a>, Azerbaijan.
On 30 December 2017, Khalilzade signed a 2.5-year contract with <a href="Gabala%20FK">Gabala FK</a>.
A year later, on 29 December 2018, Khalilzade signed 2.5-year contract with <a href="Sabah%20FK">Sabah FK</a>.
International career.
Khalilzade made his <a href="Azerbaijan%20national%20football%20team">Azerbaijan</a> debut in 2017 against <a href="San%20Marino%20national%20football%20team">San Marino</a> in <a href="2018%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20qualification">2018 FIFA World Cup qualification</a>.
